  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p><em>You convert a small sample of raw materials into a product of the same material.</em> <em>For example, you can fabricate a wooden bridge from a plank of wood, a rope from a hemp plant, and clothes from flax or wool.</em></p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><ul><li><p>You create up to 10 objects made of cloth, glass, stone, or wood (or other plant fibers). You cannot create objects made of animal material, metal, gems, or magical materials.</p></li><li><p>Any objects you make are nonmagical and inanimate.</p></li><li><p>Your chosen object(s) must fit into a 10 ft. cube.</p></li><li><p>The object can have up to two hinges and a latch (to make a container or door), but finer mechanical detail isn't possible (making a key is thus impossible).</p></li><li><p>You cannot create armor, and the only weapons you can make are simple melee weapons.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><em>If you use a sample of material that is damaged or otherwise tainted, your fabricated items are similarly affected.</em></p></div></div>",
